        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Spruce Pine, or 6 miles north of Lake James,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Table Rock, Lake James, Lake James State Park, Oak Hill, North Cove,
and Ashford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
